statements: SELECT * FROM VolunteerSchedule;
SELECT project_id, volunteer_id, start_date FROM VolunteerSchedule;
SELECT volunteer_id, end_date FROM VolunteerSchedule WHERE project_id = 1;
SELECT * FROM VolunteerSchedule ORDER BY start_date DESC;
SELECT schedule_id, project_id, volunteer_id FROM VolunteerSchedule WHERE start_date >= '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM VolunteerSchedule WHERE project_id = 1
SELECT volunteer_id, start_date, end_date FROM VolunteerSchedule WHERE volunteer_id = 5

SELECT project_id, volunteer_id, DATEDIFF(end_date, start_date) AS duration FROM VolunteerSchedule WHERE project_id = 3
SELECT DISTINCT project_id, COUNT(volunteer_id) AS volunteer_count FROM VolunteerSchedule GROUP BY project_id
SELECT * FROM organization;
SELECT organization_name FROM organization ORDER BY organization_name DESC;
SELECT schedule_date, project_name FROM volunteer_schedule WHERE volunteer_id = 1;

SELECT organization_id, organization_name FROM organization WHERE organization_id = 1;
SELECT volunteer_id, project_name, start_time, end_time FROM volunteer_schedule WHERE schedule_date BETWEEN '2022-07-01' AND '2022-07-31';

SELECT organization.organization_name, volunteer_schedule.project_name, volunteer_schedule.schedule_date FROM organization JOIN volunteer_schedule ON organization.organization_id = volunteer_schedule.volunteer_id;
SELECT organization_id, organization_name FROM organization ORDER BY organization_id DESC;

SELECT * FROM Project WHERE start_date > '2022-01-01' AND end_date < '2022-12-31';
SELECT project_name, description FROM Project ORDER BY project_name DESC;
SELECT v.name, p.project_name, s.date FROM Volunteer v JOIN Schedule s ON v.volunteer_id = s.volunteer_id JOIN Project p ON s.project_id = p.project_id WHERE s.hours_worked > 5;

SELECT v.name AS volunteer_name, p.project_name AS project_name, s.date AS work_date FROM Volunteer v, Schedule s, Project p WHERE v.volunteer_id = s.volunteer_id AND s.project_id = p.project_id AND s.date >= '2022-06-01';
